6   = 00110₂
7   = 00111₂
8   = 01000₂
9   = 01001₂
10  = 01010₂
11  = 01011₂
12  = 01100₂
13  = 01101₂
14  = 01110₂

Observation when increasing a number by 1 (from x to x + 1):

All trailing 1s are flipped to 0s.

The rightmost 0 just before those trailing 1s is flipped to 1.

All bits to the left of that position remain unchanged.
